            <div type="apparatus">
                <p>PENDING</p>
                 </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>I no longer fear God, but I love Him. For love casts out fear</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Partially preserved. A cross with arrays in the angles marks the beginning and probably the end of the text. Τhe words αὐτόν και βάλλει are misspelled. The inscription is identified with a saying of Saint Antonios from the Apophegmata Patrum (PG 65,85). The same text is proposed for the scroll of Saint Antonios in the Painter's Manual of Dionysios of Fourna (<bibl><ptr target="#Sacopoulo1966"/>,<citedRange> 105, n.1</citedRange></bibl>).</p> 
            </div>
